11#ifndef MODULES_INCLUDE_MODULE_COMMON_TYPES_H_
12#define MODULES_INCLUDE_MODULE_COMMON_TYPES_H_
13
14#include <stdint.h>
15
16#include <vector>
17
18namespace webrtc {
19
20// Interface used by the CallStats class to distribute call statistics.
21// Callbacks will be triggered as soon as the class has been registered to a
22// CallStats object using RegisterStatsObserver.
23class CallStatsObserver {
24 public:
25 virtual void OnRttUpdate(int64_t avg_rtt_ms, int64_t max_rtt_ms) = 0;
26
27 virtual ~CallStatsObserver() {}
28};
29
30// Interface used by NackModule and JitterBuffer.
31class NackSender {
32 public:
33 // If |buffering_allowed|, other feedback messages (e.g. key frame requests)
34 // may be added to the same outgoing feedback message. In that case, it's up
35 // to the user of the interface to ensure that when all buffer-able messages
36 // have been added, the feedback message is triggered.
37 virtual void SendNack(const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers,
38 bool buffering_allowed) = 0;
39
40 protected:
41 virtual ~NackSender() {}
42};
43
44// Interface used by NackModule and JitterBuffer.
45class KeyFrameRequestSender {
46 public:
47 virtual void RequestKeyFrame() = 0;
48
49 protected:
50 virtual ~KeyFrameRequestSender() {}
51};
52
53// Interface used by LossNotificationController to communicate to RtpRtcp.
54class LossNotificationSender {
55 public:
56 virtual ~LossNotificationSender() {}
57
58 virtual void SendLossNotification(uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
59 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
60 bool decodability_flag,
61 bool buffering_allowed) = 0;
62};
63
64} // namespace webrtc
65
66#endif // MODULES_INCLUDE_MODULE_COMMON_TYPES_H_
